                <head>324. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 6, 1963, Secretary-General <persName corresp="#p_UT1">U
                        Thant</persName> proposed that <persName corresp="#p_SF4">Felix
                        Schnyder</persName>’s term of office as High Commissioner for Refugees be
                    extended for 2 years, from January 1, 1964, to December 31, 1965. On November 27
                    the General Assembly decided, by acclamation, to extend <persName
                        corresp="#p_SF4">Schnyder</persName>’s term. (National Archives and Records
                    Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1960–63, REF
                    3 <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, and Yearbook of the United Nations, 1963,
                    page 367)</p>
            </div>
